[2026-04-13] ✅ **Fixed and pushed!**

## The Problem
When loading `/shared/01204ece-...`, the HTML used **relative paths** like `href="trip-planner.css"`. The browser resolved these relative to the current URL, trying to load:
- `/shared/trip-planner.css` ❌ (doesn't exist)
- `/shared/auth-service.js` ❌ (doesn't exist)

This caused MIME type errors because those paths returned 404s or HTML error pages instead of actual CSS/JS files.

## The Fix
Changed all CSS/JS references from relative to **absolute paths**

